pullrequest.title: Road textures (resubmission of Tashwin's pull request #92)

content.raw:
I've done this in the past (resubmit another person's pull request).  We should try not to do this because it subverts the fork-->pull request methodology. 

In this case is there av strong reason to resubmit tashwins pull request?
